FG-521 — Limited-Remand Launch (Task • Time • Scope • Fallback)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Kick off remand with a written instruction block everyone follows.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Quote mandate; restate Task (findings a–d) • Time (21–30d) • Scope (no expansion) • Fallback (20-min harm hearing); circulate to court & counsel; attach tick-box order.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a one-page kickoff memo quoting the mandate and pasting the 4-line block.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Remand: findings (a–d) by 21 days; scope limited; 20-min harm hearing permitted; status ≤3 pp on day 14.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Clear launch text prevents scope creep.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A narrow corridor card labeled Task/Time/Scope/Fallback.

⸻

FG-522 — Findings Worksheet (One Line per Factor + Pin)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Give the trial judge signable lines that map to pages.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Grid: Success/Harm/Equities/Public; each row = neutral sentence + pin box; checkbox Reached / Not reached; submit as [PROPOSED] Findings.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 4-row worksheet with blanks for page citations.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm: ‘Record shows timing loss (Ex A:1).’ □ Reached □ Not reached (pin: Tab 3 p.2).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: A good worksheet becomes the order.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A checklist with four lines and tiny pin slots.

⸻

FG-523 — Remand Calendar Card (Trigger • Interval • Due • Roll)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put the date math on paper on day one.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One-line footer: Order date → +21/30 → due → weekend/holiday roll (local time); print for chambers and counsel; mirror in status letters.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 4-entry calendar footer for the remand.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Remand 08/20 → +21 → 09/10 → weekend → 09/11 (11:59 PM local).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Visible math prevents slippage.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim footer bar with a calendar chip.

⸻

FG-524 — Harm-Only Hearing Script (20 Minutes, Two Pins)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: A short harm hearing should produce a line you can cite.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: 0–1 min: read mandate task; 1–6: movant proof (two pins); 6–12: response; 12–16: court Qs; 16–20: proposed finding lines read aloud.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 20-minute script with the exact finding sentence you want adopted.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Finding: ‘Harm is timing loss supported by Ex A:1; Tab 3 p.2.’”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Plan the line you want signed.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A 20-minute dial with the last slice labeled “Adopt findings.”

⸻

FG-525 — Status-On-Return Letter (≤3 Pages, Pins Only)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Back to the panel with what changed, where, and what to sign.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Quote mandate; list pages with findings (two pins); note any unreached factor; paste two-line relief; zero new facts.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a two-paragraph return letter with four pins and a relief line.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Findings at Dkt 101:2–3; Appx Tab 3 p.2. Relief: decide or clarify footnote ‘not reached.’”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Answer the instruction, not the whole case.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A short letter with a bracket “mandate → findings → relief.”

⸻

FG-526 — Scope Guard in Every Draft (Who • What • When)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: End filings with a scope sentence the panel can copy.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: “Scope: ¶__ as to parties only; sunset __ days; status day __; vendors carved out.” Paste under relief.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write one line tailored to your live order.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Scope: ¶3; parties only; sunset 21d; status day 14; vendors carved out.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Narrow asks last longer.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A bracketed paragraph with a tiny “parties only” tag.

⸻

FG-527 — Remand Evidence Ladder (Auth → Content → Factor)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: On remand, cite auth page first, then content, then factor.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: For each exhibit: Auth (902(11)/stamp/EXIF) → Content → Factor (harm/equities/public). Duplicate auth at tab front if needed.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write two auth-first cites for exhibits you’ll use.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Auth: Decl ¶4 (S-1 p.1) → Content: invoice (Tab 3 p.2) → Factor: harm (cost).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Provenance precedes persuasion.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A key icon before a page icon with a “harm” chip.

⸻

FG-528 — Findings Heatmap (Reached / Not Reached Grid)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Show visually what the court reached and skipped.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: 2×2 grid (Success/Harm/Equities/Public); shade reached/not reached; pin each cell; attach to OA/return packet.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 4-cell grid with one pin per cell.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Harm — Not reached (Dkt 18:2).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Seeing the hole invites the fix.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Four boxes; one grey “Not reached” circled.

⸻

FG-529 — Translation & Interpreter Logistics (Remand-Ready)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: If language access matters, paper the logistics with dates.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Request interpreter (format/time/slots); list documents for translation (hashed); cite policy; include two windows and a fallback.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line language-access filing with two date windows.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Interpreter for 20-min harm hearing; Tue/Wed 2–4 PM; docs A–C (SHA-256 …) for translation.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Access is schedule + specificity.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A globe + mic icon next to two date chips.

⸻

FG-530 — Remand Closeout (One Page + Tick-Box Order)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: End remand with a one-page note + signable order.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: What happened (pins), What remains (if anything), Relief (decide/clarify/limited remand); attach tick-box order; hash.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 120-word closeout and a 3-box order (Grant/Clarify/Remand).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Findings entered at Dkt 101:2–3; Appx Tab 3 p.2. Relief: decide or clarify n.3 (‘not reached’). Order attached.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Closure turns work into a decision.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A one-page card clipped to a checkbox order with a fingerprint footer.
